# UNIVERSAL PLAYWRIGHT FULL-COVERAGE RULE

Use this rule to generate production-grade Playwright tests for any frontend stack:
- React
- Angular
- Vue
- Svelte
- Next/Nuxt
- Plain HTML/JS

## Trigger Phrases

Run this workflow when user asks:
- `generate playwright tests`
- `generate all tests`
- `scan and generate tests`
- any equivalent request for complete e2e coverage

If this rule is not auto-attached for a chat-only prompt, **@mention** `.cursor/rules/playwright-automation.mdc` so the agent loads the full contract (eight files + mock data).

## Non-Negotiable Contract

Never do these:
- Skip files without explicit reason
- Skip forms, create/edit/config modals, drawers, or wizards
- Skip sort/filter/search/tab/pagination behavior when present
- Use placeholder pseudocode or `...`
- Use `page.waitForTimeout()`
- Use CSS/XPath selectors when role/label/testid is available

Always do these:
- Read source first, generate tests second
- When writing specs, follow **`.cursor/rules/playwright-spec-templates.mdc`** (sections 4a–4h) — that file holds the full templates so this rule stays smaller
- Produce runnable TypeScript Playwright specs
- Include valid data, invalid data, and edge cases
- Mock external API dependencies where needed
- Add mobile coverage variants for applicable flows
- **Create or update the feature mock-data module first** (see **Central mock data module** below), then import it from every generated spec — no duplicated literals across files
- **Emit separate physical spec files per suite type** for pages/features (see **Mandatory physical file split** below) — never “only smoke + ui” in a single file

## Mandatory physical file split (fixes under-generation)

When the user triggers generation for a **route page, feature module, or view** (anything that mounts a screen users navigate to), you **must** create **eight sibling files** next to each other under `automation-tests/` (mirror `src/` path), **not** one combined `feature.spec.ts`:

| File suffix | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `*.smoke.spec.ts` | Load, console/title, primary heading, timing, critical shell |
| `*.ui.spec.ts` | Mocked happy-path API, visible controls, loading/empty states |
| `*.form.spec.ts` | **Always** if the screen has any user-editable field + submit/next/save — includes validation, happy path, whitespace/long text; if there is no `<form>`, still treat wizard steps / field groups as form surfaces |
| `*.api.spec.ts` | `page.route()` success, 4xx/5xx, malformed JSON, network abort, slow response |
| `*.error.spec.ts` | UI error states, toast/error text, blocked actions, retry where applicable |
| `*.edge.spec.ts` | Navigation away, rapid input, XSS-ish strings, oversized payloads, double-submit |
| `*.mobile.spec.ts` | At minimum viewports **375×812**, **390×844**, **360×800**, **768×1024** (use `test.use({ viewport })` or project) |
| `*.accessibility.spec.ts` | Headings, labels, keyboard tab order, dialog focus, `aria-*` on errors |

**Forbidden shortcuts (treat as failure):**
- Delivering only `something.spec.ts` with `test("smoke:…")` and `test("ui:…")` prefixes **instead of** the eight files above for a page/feature
- Skipping `form`, `api`, `error`, `edge`, `mobile`, or `accessibility` because “the screen is simple” — **generate them**; scope tests to what the UI actually does (e.g. api specs still mock `GET` with 404/500 even if the page is mostly static)

**Components** (non-route): follow the table in **Phase 5** (complex vs simple); still add **`.interaction.spec.ts`** when there are handlers, and **never** skip **accessibility**.

## Central mock data module (mandatory)

For **each** generated feature (or each major route slug), add **one** TypeScript module that every spec imports:

- **Path:** `automation-tests/fixtures/mock-data/<feature-slug>.data.ts`  
  Example: `automation-tests/fixtures/mock-data/add-new-company.data.ts`
- **Exports (minimum):** structured objects — no scatter of magic strings in specs

```typescript
/** Example shape — extend per real fields from source */
export const addNewCompanyData = {
  valid: {
    companyLegalName: "Acme Holdings LLC",
    companyPhone: "+1 555 123 4567",
    // …every required field for happy path
  },
  invalid: {
    email: "not-an-email",
    phone: "abcdefghij",
    url: "not-a-url",
    // …one representative invalid value per validated type
  },
  edge: {
    longName: "A".repeat(500),
    unicodeDba: "Acme & Co. — 日本",
    search200: "A".repeat(200),
    whitespaceOnly: "   ",
    xssLikeText: "<script>alert(1)</script>",
  },
  api: {
    listSuccess: [{ id: "1", name: "Sample Corp" }],
    listEmpty: [],
    errorMessage: "Request failed",
  },
} as const;
```

**Rules:**
- **All** `fill()`, `selectOption()`, route `body: JSON.stringify(...)`, and expected labels in assertions that represent domain data **must** pull from this file (or small helpers exported next to it).
- **Valid / invalid / edge** sections are **required** even if some values are unused in v1 — they prevent the agent from inventing `foo`/`bar` strings at write time.
- When adding new tests, **update the data module first**, then wire specs.

**Completion gate:** list the mock-data path in `SOURCE_COVERAGE_REPORT` next to the feature’s specs.

## Phase 1 - Full Source Scan

Recursively scan:
- `src/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,vue,svelte,html}`

Process in this order:
1. Layout/shell/router files
2. Auth/guard files
3. Route/page/view files
4. Feature module files
5. Shared components and UI primitives

Build and print `FILES_TO_PROCESS`.

## Phase 2 - Feature Extraction Map

For every file, extract:
- Routes and navigation paths
- Forms and fields
- Create/update/config actions
- Sort/filter/search controls
- Tabs/steppers/accordion groups
- Tables/lists and row actions
- Modals/dialogs/drawers
- Loading, empty, and error states
- API calls and request methods
- Role/permission guards
- Accessibility hooks (role/aria/keyboard handlers)

Create:

`FEATURE_MAP[file] = { routes, forms, fields, actions, filters, search, sort, tabs, pagination, modals, api, states, a11y }`

## Phase 3 - Mandatory Form Coverage Lock

This is a blocking gate. Do not finish if unmet.

For every detected form surface (including embedded forms and modal/panel forms), create a row in:

`FORM_COVERAGE_TABLE`

Each row must include:
- `formId`
- `location` (route + component/modal)
- `fields[]`
- `requiredFields[]`
- `submitTrigger`
- `testFiles[]`

Required test minimum per form:
1. Valid submit with all required valid values
2. Empty submit required validation
3. Invalid format/type validation (where applicable)
4. Edge input test (whitespace, long input, special chars, etc.)

Required for modal/drawer/wizard forms:
1. Open form
2. Submit blocked when required fields missing
3. Error/warning shown correctly
4. Error/warning clears after correction
5. Successful submit/close behavior

Hard completion rule:
- `UNTESTED_FORMS: 0`

## Phase 4 - Universal Data Matrix

Use realistic values only.

| Type | Valid | Invalid | Edge |
|---|---|---|---|
| name | John Doe | "" | 500-char value |
| email | john.doe@testmail.com | not-an-email | a@b.c |
| password | Test@1234! | short | spaces-only |
| phone | 9876543210 | abcdefghij | 0000000000 |
| number | 25 | abc | -1, 999999, 3.14 |
| date | 2026-04-01 | 32-13-2026 | far past/future |
| textarea | useful summary text | "" | 1000-char + special chars |
| select | first valid option | none selected | last option |
| checkbox | checked | unchecked when required | toggle repeatedly |
| file | valid pdf/png | exe | oversized file |
| search | valid keyword | nonsense term | trimmed/special/200-char |

## Phase 5 - Test Generation Rules

Mirror source structure under:
- `automation-tests/` (plural — **never** `automation-test/`)

**Pages / routes / views / feature modules:** always emit the **eight** suite files listed in **Mandatory physical file split** (smoke, ui, form, api, error, edge, mobile, accessibility). **Do not** substitute a single `feature.spec.ts` with prefixed test names.

**Optional / scoped extras** (in addition to the eight, when behavior exists):
- `*.integration.spec.ts` — multi-step flows across routes or real orchestration
- Extra `*.interaction.spec.ts` only for **components** (not a substitute for page-level `form`/`api`/`error` files)

| Source file type | Spec files to generate |
|---|---|
| Page / Route / View | **smoke + ui + form + api + error + edge + mobile + accessibility** (eight files) |
| Feature module (screen-level) | **same eight** |
| Component (complex: Modal, Table, Drawer) | ui + interaction + error + edge + accessibility (+ form if it contains a form) |
| Component (simple: Button, Badge, Input) | ui + interaction + accessibility |
| Layout / Shell | smoke + ui + accessibility |

**Form detection:** any screen with inputs, selects, textareas, toggles, uploads, or wizard **Next** / **Save** / **Submit** → **must** have `*.form.spec.ts` (even if there is no native `<form>`).

### Single Entrypoint Requirement (MANDATORY)

After generating all spec files, always create/update:
- `automation-tests/index.ts`

`automation-tests/index.ts` must:
1. Import every generated `*.spec.ts` file exactly once.
2. Be the single file a user can run to execute the full suite.
3. Stay in sync when new spec files are added.

Example run command:
- `npx playwright test automation-tests/index.ts`

## Phase 6 - Behavior Matrices (Mandatory If Detected)

### Forms
- Required/optional validation
- Valid submit
- Invalid format submit
- Whitespace handling
- Enter-key submit
- Double-submit protection

### Search
- Valid term results
- No-result state
- Clear search resets
- Leading/trailing spaces
- Special characters
- Single-char query
- Very long query
- Debounce behavior (if implemented)

### Filters
- Single filter
- Multi-filter (AND behavior)
- Reset all
- Filter + search combination
- Filter persistence across pagination (if any)
- Invalid range handling (for date/range filters)

### Sorting
- Initial sort state
- Asc/desc toggle
- Column-specific sort behavior
- Sort persists with filter/search where expected

### Tabs/Steppers
- Switch each tab and verify panel content
- Active state styling/indicator
- Keyboard activation (Enter/Space where applicable)
- Step progression rules and blocked skipping (if wizard)

### Tables/Lists
- Header rendering
- Row rendering
- Empty state
- Error state
- Row actions (view/edit/delete if present)
- Pagination boundaries (first/last/next/prev when present)

### Modals/Dialogs/Drawers
- Open
- Close by X
- Close by Escape (if supported)
- Backdrop close (if supported)
- Form submit valid/invalid
- Background interaction lock (if implemented)

## Phase 7 - API + State Testing

For each API-dependent feature, include:
- Success response
- 4xx/5xx error response
- Network failure
- Slow response/loading state
- Empty response

Use deterministic `page.route()` mocks.

## Phase 8 - Accessibility Baseline

Include checks for:
- Reachable interactive elements via keyboard
- Visible labels/accessible names on controls
- Single primary heading where applicable
- Dialog focus behavior when open
- Error message association (`aria-describedby` or equivalent)

## Phase 9 - Mobile Coverage

Run relevant scenarios on:
- 375x812
- 390x844
- 360x800
- 768x1024

Mobile checks:
- Navigation usability
- Form interaction stability
- Dialog/panel fit
- Table/list overflow handling

## Phase 10 - Selector Policy

Priority order:
1. `getByTestId`
2. `getByRole`
3. `getByLabel`
4. `getByPlaceholder`
5. text match only when semantically stable

If stable selector is missing on critical actions, include:
- `// TODO: add data-testid="..."`

## Phase 11 - Completion Gate

Before final output, emit:
1. `SOURCE_COVERAGE_REPORT` — each `src/` file → list of generated `automation-tests/**/*.spec.ts` **and** `automation-tests/fixtures/mock-data/*.data.ts`
2. `FORM_COVERAGE_TABLE`
3. `UNTESTED_FORMS` count
4. `BEHAVIOR_COVERAGE_SUMMARY` for search/filter/sort/tab/modal/table/api/mobile/a11y
5. `SUITE_FILE_CHECK` — for every page/feature: confirm **eight** physical files exist (not one mega-spec); list any gap

Fail completion if any is true:
- `UNTESTED_FORMS > 0`
- detected behavior exists but no corresponding tests
- tests contain placeholders/pseudocode
- tests are not runnable TypeScript
- a page/feature is missing any of the **eight** required suite files or its **mock-data** module
- domain strings are duplicated across specs instead of being imported from the feature’s `*.data.ts`

## Final Rule

When in doubt, generate more targeted tests rather than skipping behavior.
Coverage completeness is higher priority than brevity.


## Appendix — Execution order (single document; no duplicate front matter)

When a trigger phrase is used: **stop passively summarizing** — run Phase 1 → 11, then the blocks below, then the **Execution checklist**.

### Analysis card — output path (use everywhere)

- Use **`automation-tests/`** mirroring `src/` (plural). Do **not** use `automation-test/`.
- **Before specs:** add/update `automation-tests/fixtures/mock-data/<slug>.data.ts` with `valid`, `invalid`, `edge`, `api` (see **Central mock data module**).
- **Each spec file** starts with imports from that module for fills, route bodies, and repeated strings.

### Spec templates

Read **`.cursor/rules/playwright-spec-templates.mdc`** sections **4a–4h** and substitute `[FeatureName]`, routes, endpoints. Prefer `page.goto('/path')` when `playwright.config.ts` defines `baseURL`.

### CRUD minimum test counts (distribute across form / api / error / edge)

**CREATE (≥11):** all required valid; all fields optional+required; all empty; partial required; duplicate error; max length; invalid format per type; Enter submit; double-submit; whitespace-only; 1000-char text.

**READ (≥5):** list + headers; empty list UI; API 500 UI; single row edge.

**UPDATE (≥9):** prefill; one-field save; all-field save; clear required; invalid in edit; cancel; navigate-away warning if any; concurrent tabs if feasible; special chars.

**DELETE (≥7):** confirm open; confirm success; direct URL after delete; cancel; stale delete; delete last; delete from filtered list.

### Search / filter / pagination (when detected)

**Search (≥8):** valid term; no results; clear; leading/trailing spaces; special chars; single char; 200-char; debounce if implemented.

**Filters (≥6):** single; multi AND; reset; filter+search; filter+paginate; invalid date range.

**Pagination (≥8):** page 1; next + URL; prev; last page next disabled; first prev disabled; page size change; search resets page; filter resets page.

### Master index and docs

- Create/update **`automation-tests/index.ts`** — import every `*.spec.ts` once.
- Optionally document commands in **`automation-tests/README.md`** (only if the repo does not already document E2E).

### Playwright tooling (project root)

1. Ensure **`@playwright/test`** in `package.json`; run **`npx playwright install`** when needed.
2. Align **`playwright.config.ts`** `baseURL` / `webServer` port with the real dev server.
3. Add scripts if missing: `test:e2e`, `test:e2e:headed`, `test:e2e:ui`, `test:e2e:debug`, `test:e2e:chromium`, `test:e2e:report`, `playwright:install`.
4. After generation: run the **full** suite (e.g. `npm run test:e2e`) and fix failures before declaring done.

